'''Juraj Ratkaj''' (also known as '''Juraj Rattkay''', born in [[Veliki Tabor]], [[Croatia]] on December 22, 1612 &mdash; [[Zagreb]], [[Croatia]], on September 1, 1666) was a [[Croatian people|Croatian]] [[historian]]. Born in the [[House of Ratkaj|Ratkaj]] noble family, barons of [[Veliki Tabor Castle|Veliki Tabor]], he was a member of the [[Society of Jesus]]. Later on he became a [[priest]] and the [[canon (priest)|canon]] of [[Zagreb]]. He took part in the [[Thirty Years' War]] in 1647 and fought the [[Ottomans]] as well. His best known work is ''Memoria regum et banorum regnorum Dalmatiae, Croatiae et Sclavoniae''.

