{{Orphan|date=January 2017}}
[[File:Marcus Bains Line.png|thumb|Marcus Bains line showing in [[KDE]]'s calendar application [[Kontact]].]] The '''Marcus Bains line''' is a line that shows the current time in many calendar applications and [[Personal information manager|PIM]] suites. Usually, it is a red horizontal line showing at the location of the current time in the "day" or "week" views of a calendar, sometimes complemented with the current time.
==History== From at least September 2000 on, there has been a patch for [[ical (Unix)|ical]] to show the Marcus Bains line.<ref>[http://www.keysduplicated.com/~ali/marcus-bains-line/ Marcus Bains Line: A Necessary Feature for Every Calendar Program] by Ali Rahimi (Oct 20, 2000. Last Updated Oct 3, 2009)</ref> Gradually other programs such as [[Korganizer]], [[Evolution (software)|Evolution]] and [[Google Calendar]] started supporting the line, either through patches, third-party scripts or natively. Many commercial programs implementing it kept the red colour or the name.
