'''Mirko Androić''' ({{IPA-sh|mǐːrko ǎndroitɕ|hr}}; 8 July 1922, in [[Varaždin]], [[Yugoslavia]] &ndash; 7 June 1982) was a [[Croatian people|Croatian]] [[historian]] and [[archivist]].<ref>Susan K. Kinnell ''People in World History: A-M''  1989 "MIRKO ANDROIC [Mirko Androić]. Arhivski Vjesnik [Yugoslavia] 1982 25: 117-118. Mirko Androić was born on 8 July 1922 in Varazdin, Yugoslavia and died on 7 June 1982."</ref> He studied [[philosophy]] at the [[University of Zagreb]], then worked as historian and chief archivist of his home town Varaždin.<ref>Historijski zbornik: v38  Povijesno društvo Hrvatske, Društvo za hrvatsku povjesnicu - 1985 Petar Strčić "MIRKO ANDROIC U arhivskoj službi SRH na naročit se način izdvajao Mirko Androić (Varaždin, 8. 7. 1922 — 7. 6. 1982) — i kao arhivist i kao historičar. Završivši povijest na Filozofskom fakultetu u Zagrebu, a bazirajući i na ..."</ref> His area of historical study was on the history of political movements in northern [[Croatia]] during the 18th Century.<ref>Mirko Androić et al., Varaždin u XVIII. stolječu i politicko-kameralni studij 1769-1969 [Varazdin in the 18th Century and the Political-Cameral School] , Zagreb - Varazdin 1972.</ref>

