{{Infobox UN resolution |number = 270 |organ = SC |date = August 26 |year = 1969 |meeting = 1,504 |code = S/RES/270 |document = https://undocs.org/S/RES/270(1969) |for = |abstention = |against = |subject = The situation in the Middle East |result = Adopted |image = |caption = }}
'''[[United Nations]] [[List of UN Security Council Resolutions|Security Council Resolution]] 270''', adopted on August 26, 1969, after an air attack by [[Israel]] on [[Southern Lebanon]], the Council condemned Israel and deplored all incidents in violation of the cease-fire and the extension of the area of fighting. The Council also declared that such grave violations of the cease-fire could not be tolerated and that the Council would have to consider further and more effective steps as envisaged in the Charter.
The resolution was adopted without vote.
